# {{lb|en|mathematics}} [[oneness|Oneness]], [[singularity]], seen as a component of a [[whole number]]; a magnitude of one. {{defdate|from 16th c.}}
#*'''1570''', {{w|John Dee}}, in H. Billingsley (trans.) Euclid, ''Elements of Geometry'', Preface:
#*:''Number'', we define, to be, a certayne Mathematicall Sũme, of '''''Vnits'''''. [Note the worde, Vnit, to expresse the Greke Monas, & not Vnitie: as we haue all, commonly, till now, vsed.]
# {{lb|en|sciences}} A [[standard]] measure of a quantity.
#: ''The centimetre is a '''unit''' of length.''
# The [[number]] [[one]].
# {{clipping of|en|international unit}}
#: ''This pill provides 500 '''units''' of Vitamin E.''
# An organized group comprising people and/or equipment.
#: ''He was a member of a special police '''unit'''.''
# {{lb|en|military|informal}} A member of a military organization.
#: ''The fifth tank brigade moved in with 20 '''units'''.'' (''i.e., 20 tanks'')
# {{lb|en|US|military}} Any military [[element]] whose [[structure]] is [[prescribed]] by competent [[authority]], such as a [[table of organization and equipment]]; specifically, part of an [[organization]]<ref name="JP102">'''Joint Publication 1-02 ''U.S. Department of Defense Dictionary of Military and Associated Terms; 12 April 2001 (As Amended Through 14 April 2006).'''''</ref>.
# {{lb|en|US|military}} An organization [[title]] of a [[subdivision]] of a [[group]] in a [[task force]]<ref name="JP102"/>.
# {{lb|en|US|military}} A [[standard]] or [[basic]] quantity into which an item of supply is [[divided]], [[issued]]{{,}} or [[detailed]]. In this meaning, also called [[unit of issue]]<ref name="JP102"/>.
# {{lb|en|US|military}} With regard to Reserve Components of the Armed Forces, denotes a [[Selected Reserve]] unit organized, equipped, and trained for [[mobilization]] to serve on [[active duty]] as a unit or to [[augment]] or be augmented by another unit. Headquarters and support functions without wartime missions are not considered units<ref name="JP102"/>.
# {{lb|en|algebra}} The identity element, neutral element.
# {{lb|en|algebra}} An element having an [[inverse]], an invertible element; an [[associate]] of the [[unity]].
#: {{hypernyms|en|regular element}}
# {{lb|en|category theory}} In an [[adjunction]], a [[natural transformation]] from the [[identity functor]] of the domain of the left [[adjoint functor]] to the composition of the right adjoint functor with the left adjoint functor.
# {{lb|en|geology}} A volume of [[rock]] or [[ice]] of identifiable [[origin]] and [[age]] range that is defined by the [[distinctive]] and [[dominant]], easily [[mapped]] and recognizable [[petrographic]], [[lithologic]] or [[paleontologic]] features ([[facies]]) that characterize it.
# {{lb|en|commerce}} An item which may be sold singly.
#: ''We shipped nearly twice as many '''units''' this month as last month.''
# {{lb|en|UK}} A [[unit of alcohol]].
# {{lb|en|UK|electricity}} One [[kilowatt-hour]] (as recorded on an [[electricity meter]]).
# {{lb|en|US|Australia|New Zealand}} a measure of housing equivalent to the living quarters of one [[household]]; an [[apartment]] where a group of apartments is contained in one or more multi-storied buildings or a group of dwellings is in one or more single storey buildings, usually arranged around a driveway.
# {{lb|en|historical}} A [[gold]] [[coin]] of the [[reign]] of James I, worth twenty [[shilling]]s.
#: {{rfquotek|en|Camden}}
# A [[work unit]].
# {{lb|en|UK|slang}} A physically large person.
#* '''2018''', 11 December, BBC News, ''[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-beds-bucks-herts-46519800 Aylesbury goalkeeper, 14, dies after match injury]''
#*: Luca's father, Americo Campanaro, said: "I feel like my heart has been ripped out."<br>Mr Campanaro added: "He was a big lad, a big '''unit''', that's why he was a goalkeeper, with a big heart to match. A gentle giant."

